            <div class="service-icon"><i class="fa fa-quote-right"></i></div>
            
            <h3>Definition</h3>
            
            <p>
              The word <em>Doula</em> (prounounced 'doo-la') is a Greek word meaning 'woman or caregiver'.
              Refers to someone who offers emotional or physical support to a woman and her partner before, 
              during, and after childbirth.  A doula is also known as a birth assistant.
            </p>
            
            
          </div>
        
          <div class="col-sm-4 service-item color1 scrollimation scale-in d1">
          
            <div class="service-icon"><i class="fa fa-cog "></i></div>
            
            <h3>Function</h3>
            
            <p>My dream is for every woman to get the support she deserves, so she is able to have the kind of birth she wants, whatever it may be.  I support fully, wholeheartedly, with complete acceptance. </p>
            
            
          </div>
          
          <div class="col-sm-4 service-item color2 scrollimation scale-in d2">
          
            <div class="service-icon"><i class="fa fa-smile-o"></i></div>
            
            <h3>Promise</h3>
            
            <p>
              <ol class="text-left">
              <li>You cannot hurt my feelings.</li>
              <li>I won't lie to you.</li>
              <li>I will do everything in my power so you won't suffer.</li>
              <li>I will help you feel safe.</li>
              <li>I cannot speak for you; but I will make sure that you have a voice and that you are heard.</li>
              </ol>
            </p>
            
          </div>
          
